	<!-- message -->
	<p>A few couple notes from a troll point of view:<br />
<br />
1) Dont get bothered by the twinks.  The thing about pvp server twinks is they never lvl.  Just keep grinding the exp and eventually you will be 8 lvls higher then them.  At that point, no matter what they have for gear, you are gonna get your sweet revenge.<br />
<br />
2) Like the above poster said, if you dont plan on progressing very fast or at all, i would not suggest getting in range of 65 lvl chars. ~i am guilty of this and i pay for it dearly sometimes~  They will resist every time and you wont, end of story.  But if you do want to progress, ya evetually you will need to lvl, but try to find a guild that is already started in progression so you will have a good gang to back you up when needed.<br />
<br />
3) Dont carry very much coin (at least on VZ/TZ). When you die, all the coin you had is now in the pkers pockets.<br />
<br />
4) Get a close grp of friends and stick by them.  On tz people like to get "hunting parties" together and go kill people soloing or small grps.  But most often if they see 5 or 6 people they will leave the grp alone, or attack and then its all fun because the numbers are even.<br />
<br />
5) Give the trolls hugs from time to time.  We lost our city a while back and we are still not over it, we need the lovin.<br />
<br />
6) Look me up if you need help on quests/gear camps.  I usually solo when i get online unless i get an ldon grp and if im free, im more then happy to help a shaman out.  Even if you are a barbie or a kitty.  Frogs im still getting to like just cause you are a shaman and the spirits would not like me to kill you.<br />
<br />
FYI that is all coming from a TZ point of view.  I dont play the hardcore pvp servers, but i like my home and i would suggest it.  But dont let the (pvp-teams) tag fol you, there are no more teams, at least by guild standards.  Every guild now is xteam, save a few dark only guilds.  Most people will respect you no matter your race, and the ones who dont will let you know very clearly.<br />
<br />
My 2cp...</p>
	
	
	
