	<!-- message -->
	<p>Asta gave a pretty good image of PVP. It's like EQ with the extra flavor of uncertainity of when you will be ambushed by 3x woodelves hell bent on beating the snot out of you etc.<br />
<br />
Mass-pvp is a great thing, imagine whole guilds having away at eachother all over the zone.<br />
<br />
Regarding loot:<br />
<br />
Vallon Zek and Tallon Zek only allows looting of coins.<br />
<br />
Rallos Zek allows looting of droppable items except for your main and offhand (correct me if im wrong).<br />
<br />
Sullon Zek, im not sure about.<br />
<br />
* * *<br />
<br />
As a shaman, you will be good up to lvl 52 (like Asta said). At lvl 65 you have problems dealing damage due to resists and dots being curable. You might find it easy to stay alive though because you can outrun and outheal many classes.<br />
<br />
At lvl 65 your main PVP strength comes in mass-pvp (from one group encounters and up). Shamans can debuff and heal and be a great support to the more offensive classes.<br />
<br />
Oh, and stay away from bards, they need to eat the Nerf Bat in PVP, badly...</p>
	
	
	
