	<!-- message -->
	<p>Rallos loot rules include one piece of droppable gear (not main hand/offhand/range/ammo iirc) and cash, its also ffa pvp withing 5 lvls.<br />
Sullon is ffa pvp for ALL lvls after you ding lvl 6. yes a lvl 65 can gank you at lvl 6. there are 3 HARD coded teams, you cant heal or help the other teams in pvp so no worries about some evil killing your good while his goodie cleric heals him and you cant do anything about it. Sullon loot is cash + you get an insignia thats virtually garbage because sony was on crack when they implimented the system. the advice for shaman is valid, stay low 50's or be prepared to lose every time you fight. its possible to malos and then dump your entire mana bar on someone and end up with them at 100% life thanks to gimped spells and messed up resists.<br />
<br />
I havent ever played blue so I really cant compare the 2.<br />
<br />
look me up on Sullon if you roll up a good or a n00t,(I can give you some minor twink stuff easy enough) if you plan on rolling evil you might as well stay on your blue server.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
