<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>CasmussSZ</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Initiate<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jun 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Yeah, I wouldn't reccommend starting a shaman on sullon. There isn't much low level pvp to be had. It is a gankfest, and shaman aren't exactly the best gankers. If you plan on making it to higher levels, it can be done without too much trouble due to the server xp bonus and the very low population. If you scout around a bit, you'll find you can have many zones to yourself. The downside is that at higher levels, you can't land a spell as a shaman on anyone with decent gear, so solo pvp is pretty much out. PvP in groups can be pretty cool, but lamers usually turn it into a trainfest. At least they made a rule against same team training now - that was a nightmare that you won't have to deal with if you come to Sullon. Hopefully the promised pvp changes will address make shaman more viable in high end pvp, but I'm not holding my breath. Good luck on whatever server you choose!</p>
	
	
	
	
	
