	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>howler</b><br /><i><br />
But back in the day, to get to that point meant you had to deal with me for the first 55 levels and I ensured that your night, everynight, was hell.  If I didn't kill you, I'd follow you around and make sure you had ensnare on you, everywhere you went.  The people on zeks are real bastards.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I guess it takes all kinds but this is exactly why I think PvP are over run with little kids (only speaking from a few weeks experience on VZ).  It's the mentality of I'd rather spend my time slowing you down than being "productive".  Dont get me wrong... I see the attraction of sneaking around someone fighting a mob waiting till he's beat up and cant defend himself before attacking...er...well... okay I dont.  But still if it's your thing then I guess that's cool.<br />
<br />
I do find it funny how folks on Red servers feel the need to hold their status as a Red player over the Blubies.  Me, I like hanging out with friends going and wailing on mobs and progressing.... maybe if I had a lot more time I'd play on a Red server because you can progress slower.  But considering I work from 6 to 8 most days when I do get to play I dont want my whole night ruined by a some random guy running past looking for kicks.  <br />
<br />
Like I said it takes all kinds and I gave it a shot but it wasnt for me.  I think everyone should try it for a bit and if you enjoy it stick with it because it's 100% different than the EQ on Blubie servers.  OH and if folks do give the neg rep bumps "Shut up blubie!" at least post your name <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /></p>
	
	
	
