	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>howler</b><br /><i>Another thought that just came to me.  I've said this a number of times and been scoffed at, especially by people in guilds at the higher end.  You'll never play the game at a higher skill level than when you do on a no rules server.  If you start from the bottom on a zek and work your way up to the top without help, especially on sullon where anybody and everybody can and will try to kill you, you deserve to be there.  <br />
<br />
I won't lie to you though, most of the pvp you see there won't be pvp.  Bards will be training you like it's their job.  Wizards and Shadowknights are phenomenal gankers.  Pvp is about killing, it's not about honor or what is right.  There is no morality to it.  It's about the adrenaline rush you get from knowing that you just caused a person hundreds of miles away a night of endless agony.  It's about sneaking up on that wizard who just manaburned you when he is in the middle of a kite, and dispelling his mobs so that he eats an experience death.  You may not think you will enjoy those sorts of things, but very few things on blue servers will match the real threat of player vs. player combat and the addiction of that adrenaline rush.  <br />
<br />
But back in the day, to get to that point meant you had to deal with me for the first 55 levels and I ensured that your night, everynight, was hell.  If I didn't kill you, I'd follow you around and make sure you had ensnare on you, everywhere you went.  The people on zeks are real bastards.<br />
<br />
My best experience in EQ was the first time I got revenge against another player.  Was playing on Rallos with my lvl 15 shaman, soloing down in Kurns tower.  Here's me, my first red character, quietly leveling away.  Had earned myself a couple pieces of leather armor, and wracked up a couple plat after 4 hours.  It was going to buy my new spells and I was about to ding.  I wasn't really paying attention, I didn't know any better.  I didn't check to see who else was in the zone, why would I have.  Within moments, an ugly twinked out sk ran down and ganked my few plat.  Didn't get my level, couldn't buy my spells, lost my corpse.  Found him the next day, fighting a badger, deep under kurns.  He was at 10 life when he killed the badger and bent down to loot it, still unaware I was watching him.  One nuke and he was dead.  Walked over and intended to get my leather bp back he stole from me the day before.  He was wearing a cloth bp but I took it anyways, just to spite him.  It wasn't until he sent me hate messages that I realized I looted his fungi.<br />
<br />
That's why you'll love pvp.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>ROFL thats brilliant, that is honestly the best success I have ever heard of in years of EQ>.<br />
<br />
Grats L<img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /></p>
	
	
	
