	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Gunny</b><br /><i>Do you guys that play on these PVP servers have like, arch-rivals? Certain PCs that go out their way to mess with your game specificly, and vise versa? And can rangers track PCs on these servers?<br />
</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Was camping stormfeather for the haste mask.  Had been at it for over a week now, and was at the end of a 19 hour stretch that night.  If you know much about the quest, you know that this part of it is probably the most frustrating of all.  Well he was going to spawn any minute and I was ready for him.  <br />
<br />
There was this level 30ish gnome magician who had been pestering me now for the past 5 hours.  Really had to give this kid credit.  I've got well over 100 aa invested in this ranger and at the time, being a hunter was the equivalent of being a monster in the pvp arena, especially against casters.  But he's level 30 something and he knows why I'm there and he wants to hunt cougars.  Well, being a ranger, I'm a nature nut, so I swore to protect all the cougars.  I just couldn't have anybody killing my pals.<br />
<br />
My bird is about to spawn and I could tell this kid was about ready to mount another attack on me.  I had stopped killing him with my stonewood an hour or so back and resorted to just kicking him to death to amuse myself.  This must have been the 9th time he's done this.  Well he sent his pet up after me and drilled me with a nuke.  Nothing big, just annoying.  But he ran away this time, came back a minute later and did it again, and then again a minute after that.  Now I don't mind you sacrificing yourself on my sword, but you don't taunt me like that.  <br />
<br />
I chased his gnome arse down half way across the zone the next time he did it, and I killed him.  But before I wallopped him, he says to me, "my friend tells me that stormfeather just popped, thanks for the 'second part of an Iceclad map' jackass."  I still remember that.<br />
<br />
For the next half hour, I kept that kid ensnared and unconscious.  Not dead, no, he had already shown me death didn't mean too much too him.  After that he was on my friends list, and everytime I saw him up, I had my friends in his guild tell me where he was so I could repeat the process.  He quit the character after two weeks of daily torture.<br />
<br />
Never get between a vengeful ranger and his quarry.  You may get your level 30 buddy his quest piece, but you'll pay a price.</p>
	
	
	
