</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I played on tallon when it opened. it used to be a blast with the occasional ganker.<br />
If you have ever complained or thought classes were not balanced on a bvluebie server DONT PVP.<br />
Class balance is even worse in PVP.<br />
<br />
The cross teaming aspect will on occasion ruin your DAY. nothing worse then having a fight where you cannot attack the cleric cause they are the same race you are while they CH the enemy tank beating you like a rag doll.<br />
<br />
Also nothing worse they having some immature moron get his kicks ruining your evening.<br />
<br />
I LOVE PVP but unfortunately the code in this game was bluebie minded with PVP as an after thought so the exploits are plentiful.<br />
<br />
My heart has never beat so hard in bluebie fights like is has for PVP.<br />
Its been years since I stopped playing on Tallon and I still have the screenshots from those memorable kills.<br />
<br />
Not to mention ended up guilded with some of my rivals from tallon on other games like DAOC. The friends we made will last.<br />
<br />
It will be really good times and some really suck ass times. whiners have louder voices. Getting killed by other players by getting trained will no longer be a Dammit man why didnt you yell train its a dammit how will I get my body back without the arse doing it agaion.<br />
<br />
Both types of players will be there the really nice players and the aholes. the difference is the aholes have more ability to harash you directly. and the nicer people have a closer bond due to power in numbers.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
