</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Sullon is what you make of it.<br />
<br />
Players like virtually any other server and run the full spectrum of personality types, however the ruleset allows players to visibly hamper and harm another player with more options and so the cases of griefing and stupidity that exist on ALL servers is simply more visible.<br />
<br />
I do disagree with Ninth on some of what he said.  The teams are horribly unbalanced, which is one of the reasons I left, however the ranger nerf wasn't prompted by SZ, there are 4 pvp servers, and the changes that went forward were part of the dev team.  Gm's may indeed tip balance in game, and bring outright bias to the teams, but affecting class balance in PvP and game coding isn't in their bag of tricks.<br />
<br />
The same options for philanthropy that Glor listed also still exist on the reds, on SZ a hard coded team server, nothing stops you from protecting and helping gear your newbies...the choice to do so is up to you.<br />
<br />
Gunny the best thing I can suggest is just make a toon and log on.  If you don't like that rule set, then simply create a different character on another red server.  It wont cost you anything and you might get a feel for the server.<br />
<br />
I left SZ due to class imbalances that I encoutered while seeking combat.  I had never used burn in PvP, and refused to do so as I considered it a gimp skill, however the perception of my class and how it changed in PvP with the release of SoL made it more difficult to find good fights, which previously I had no problems finding.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Valkargen Mightypuppy<br />
Elder Prophet of Brell</div>
	
	
