<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>FreyrSZ</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Lurker<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Aug 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I play on SZ, on the fairly underpowered good team.  SZ PvP isn't for everyone, you have to be ready to be griefed, trained, ganked, burned, faction burned, and every other possible way of killing you.  In terms of Shaman PvP, we tend to not do very well against people with good resists.  More or less you'd have to pick your fights against crap geared evens, hope spear of torment will gank someone in group pvp, or grief greeny (something everyone does and has had done to them).  <br />
<br />
In terms of rules:<br />
-20% exp bonus on SZ $$<br />
-Debuffs take off an extra 50% vs. saves (minorly helpful)<br />
-You can't be killed under 6 in most newbies zones BUT if you leave the newbie zones and are under 6 you can and will be killed<br />
-PvP deaths to even cons (or green cons) will cost you exp/coin, if you die to an even past level 20 you drop an Insignia (called a coin) of your respective deity<br />
-Falling/Drowning deaths don't take exp<br />
<br />
The server is pretty fun (at least in my opinion), but you have to not get bothered by being repeatedly and irrationally killed, otherwise you won't last a week.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Venerable Freyr<br />
Froglok Prophet of Sullon Zek</div>
	
	
